Cooking Tutorial

Cowboy Caviar

Ingredients


FOR THE DRESSING:

1/3 c. extra-virgin olive oil 1/3 c. lime juice 3 tbsp. chopped fresh cilantro 1 tbsp. hot sauce (such as Cholula) 1/2 tsp. cumin 1 tsp. kosher salt

FOR THE SALAD:

1 c. black beans 1 small red onion, finely chopped 1 c. corn kernels 1 c. cherry tomatoes, quartered 1 c. black-eyed peas 2 orange bell peppers, chopped 1 avocado, chopped Tortilla chips, for serving

Instructions

Step 1

Slice the avocado in half, smash it with a fork. It doesn’t have to be perfect or lump-free.

Step 2

Add the Himalayan salt and the garlic powder to taste. Spread the mix on the toast and add the spinach (wash well before consumption).
